knight fellowships class of 2009 chanda chisala knight fellowships chanda chisala chanda chisala international fellow president and editor zambia online lusaka zambia study focus the impact of the internet on the future of african journalism and the philosophy of human rights chisala was born in chingola zambia and earned his bachelor's degree from the university of zambia in 1997 he founded moneynet enterprises and started zambia's first portal site zambia online www zambia co zm today moneynet remains zambia's leading online media company developing sites for numerous organizations including one for the post zambia's largest independent newspaper as president and editor of zambia online chisala was also its first reporter covering a wide range of topics including politics and economic development his political articles have also been published in all the major newspapers of zambia fellows are listed with original titles and employers from their fellowship year stanford university
